863
00:36:19,820 --> 00:36:21,100
and complaining is one of them.

864
00:36:21,540 --> 00:36:22,380
My wife

865
00:36:22,820 --> 00:36:23,660
has a sharp tongue.

866
00:36:23,820 --> 00:36:24,860
She complains all the time.

867
00:36:24,930 --> 00:36:26,220
People say I'm afraid of her,

868
00:36:26,380 --> 00:36:27,380
but I don't think so.

869
00:36:27,380 --> 00:36:29,340
I actually feel proud

870
00:36:29,500 --> 00:36:30,540
of her complaints.

871
00:36:30,540 --> 00:36:31,980
It shows how much she cares.

872
00:36:31,980 --> 00:36:33,140
I'm happy about that.

873
00:36:33,970 --> 00:36:35,140
You're happy,

874
00:36:35,580 --> 00:36:36,860
unlike me...

875
00:36:38,710 --> 00:36:39,350
Qiming,

876
00:36:39,420 --> 00:36:40,460
we were talking about Chen,

877
00:36:40,460 --> 00:36:42,440
and now you've turned it into
something about you.

878
00:36:42,540 --> 00:36:43,380
What happened?

879
00:36:43,620 --> 00:36:44,460
It's a long story.

880
00:36:44,620 --> 00:36:45,900
Go ahead, speak up.

881
00:36:46,140 --> 00:36:48,060
Since you're here,
and you're more cultured,

882
00:36:48,420 --> 00:36:49,540
maybe you can help me out.

883
00:36:49,620 --> 00:36:50,900
I just can't figure out

884
00:36:51,220 --> 00:36:52,540
what she meant.

885
00:36:52,940 --> 00:36:54,420
Help me out here.

886
00:36:54,420 --> 00:36:55,260
What is it?

887
00:36:58,460 --> 00:36:59,460
A poem?

888
00:37:00,980 --> 00:37:03,460
Sometimes I think, in this marriage,

889
00:37:03,820 --> 00:37:04,980
from start to finish,

890
00:37:05,620 --> 00:37:07,420
it's only me holding everything together.

891
00:37:08,820 --> 00:37:09,660
Tell me,

892
00:37:09,860 --> 00:37:11,180
what's the real point

893
00:37:11,460 --> 00:37:12,900
for a woman to get married?

894
00:37:13,220 --> 00:37:15,540
But Chen works so hard

895
00:37:15,700 --> 00:37:17,150
for the family, doesn't he?

896
00:37:17,420 --> 00:37:18,740
No, it's all for himself.

897
00:37:23,910 --> 00:37:24,750
Xiu'e,

898
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:26,980
I envy you and Aiping

899
00:37:28,220 --> 00:37:29,940
so much.

900
00:37:31,100 --> 00:37:31,940
And Pei too.

901
00:37:32,660 --> 00:37:33,820
She and Liu Songming

902
00:37:33,820 --> 00:37:35,280
argue all the time, but at least

903
00:37:35,500 --> 00:37:37,020
it shows they have some chemistry.

904
00:37:38,380 --> 00:37:39,220
Not like me.

905
00:37:40,060 --> 00:37:41,740
My home feels so cold.

906
00:37:41,740 --> 00:37:42,660
When he gets angry,

907
00:37:43,100 --> 00:37:44,740
I don't dare even to speak.

908
00:37:49,220 --> 00:37:50,660
Come on, it's alright.

909
00:37:53,220 --> 00:37:56,540
Men… you have to take it slow.

910
00:38:03,020 --> 00:38:03,980
Even if you get angry,

911
00:38:03,980 --> 00:38:05,260
you will still clean up.

912
00:38:07,060 --> 00:38:08,860
I can't just sit around.

913
00:38:09,060 --> 00:38:10,940
When I'm feeling down,

914
00:38:10,940 --> 00:38:12,540
cleaning helps me feel better.

915
00:38:12,940 --> 00:38:14,020
Good for you.

916
00:38:14,020 --> 00:38:15,140
As for me, no matter my mood,

917
00:38:15,140 --> 00:38:16,420
I always do housework.

918
00:38:16,820 --> 00:38:18,060
Let me help you.

919
00:38:18,500 --> 00:38:19,620
No, sit here. Leave it to me.

920
00:38:19,620 --> 00:38:21,180
It's fine! I'm used to it.

921
00:38:21,180 --> 00:38:22,020
Come on.

922
00:38:22,060 --> 00:38:24,060
"Already lightly powdered"

923
00:38:24,240 --> 00:38:25,920
means she stopped
wearing makeup long ago.

924
00:38:26,380 --> 00:38:27,580
The second line,

925
00:38:27,940 --> 00:38:28,980
"alone in an empty room",

926
00:38:28,980 --> 00:38:30,030
I think I understand that.

927
00:38:30,420 --> 00:38:31,980
It's about feeling lonely, right?

928
00:38:31,980 --> 00:38:32,980
Am I right?

929
00:38:32,980 --> 00:38:33,820
Yes, yes.

930
00:38:33,940 --> 00:38:36,060
It means living alone in an empty room.

931
00:38:37,140 --> 00:38:37,980
And

932
00:38:39,060 --> 00:38:41,180
"wishing to resume a broken string

933
00:38:41,620 --> 00:38:43,180
but cannot" means trying to fix

934
00:38:43,180 --> 00:38:44,100
a broken string.

935
00:38:44,260 --> 00:38:45,340
What it expresses is…

936
00:38:45,740 --> 00:38:47,540
wishing to find someone to replace you,

937
00:38:47,980 --> 00:38:50,540
but not being able to.

938
00:38:52,220 --> 00:38:53,060
Got it?

939
00:38:53,620 --> 00:38:54,620
Got it?

940
00:38:56,060 --> 00:38:57,620
When you put it all together,

941
00:38:57,620 --> 00:38:58,860
this poem

942
00:38:58,860 --> 00:39:00,940
is about a woman's sorrow.

943
00:39:01,420 --> 00:39:02,540
But back in ancient times,

944
00:39:03,060 --> 00:39:04,740
male poets sometimes

945
00:39:05,140 --> 00:39:07,220
used these kinds of women's lament poems

946
00:39:07,220 --> 00:39:10,140
to express their own
frustrations with their careers

947
00:39:10,140 --> 00:39:13,180
or their feelings of loneliness.

948
00:39:13,380 --> 00:39:14,220
Got it?

949
00:39:14,700 --> 00:39:15,540
Got it?

950
00:39:16,460 --> 00:39:19,060
This was written by a woman.

951
00:39:20,940 --> 00:39:21,820
Aiping wrote it?

952
00:39:25,420 --> 00:39:26,260
Kang.

953
00:39:26,540 --> 00:39:27,380
Mr. Chen.

954
00:39:28,140 --> 00:39:29,020
I... I'm...

955
00:39:29,020 --> 00:39:29,860
I'm not

956
00:39:29,940 --> 00:39:30,860
expecting Guan Aiping

957
00:39:31,180 --> 00:39:32,940
to forget Xiao Youguang right away.

958
00:39:33,140 --> 00:39:34,140
That's not what I expect.

959
00:39:34,140 --> 00:39:34,980
I can accept it.

960
00:39:35,220 --> 00:39:36,940
We're both older now,

961
00:39:36,940 --> 00:39:38,060
and we know everyone

962
00:39:38,060 --> 00:39:39,220
has a past.

963
00:39:39,700 --> 00:39:41,580
Honestly, it doesn't bother me.

964
00:39:44,260 --> 00:39:45,540
She… "wishes to resume"…

965
00:39:45,740 --> 00:39:47,060
She's actually looking for someone

966
00:39:47,500 --> 00:39:50,020
to replace Xiao Youguang,
but she hasn't found

967
00:39:50,020 --> 00:39:51,060
that person.

968
00:39:52,420 --> 00:39:53,700
As for the "broken string"…

969
00:39:55,700 --> 00:39:56,540
I'm not...

970
00:39:56,540 --> 00:39:57,460
a musician.

971
00:39:57,460 --> 00:39:58,300
I...

972
00:39:58,900 --> 00:40:00,340
I can't even sing in tune…

973
00:40:00,340 --> 00:40:01,180
I'm like a mute!

974
00:40:01,620 --> 00:40:02,460
I'm nothing...

975
00:40:05,060 --> 00:40:05,900
Why are you laughing?

976
00:40:08,620 --> 00:40:09,980
I wasn't feeling great today,

977
00:40:09,980 --> 00:40:11,580
but now I feel better.

978
00:40:13,150 --> 00:40:14,380
Let's all be happy!

979
00:40:16,790 --> 00:40:17,900
Oh, women…

980
00:40:20,580 --> 00:40:21,540
A woman's heart is like

981
00:40:22,380 --> 00:40:23,240
a needle in the ocean.

982
00:40:24,380 --> 00:40:25,820
You two each take a drink.

983
00:40:25,820 --> 00:40:26,940
Come on, have a drink.

984
00:40:26,940 --> 00:40:28,820
Sir, can we get another bottle
of soft drink?

985
00:40:53,660 --> 00:40:54,700
What's this?

986
00:40:55,100 --> 00:40:55,940
No idea.

987
00:41:04,060 --> 00:41:04,900
Look here.

988
00:41:04,940 --> 00:41:06,540
A boy and a girl,

989
00:41:06,660 --> 00:41:09,500
with some little hearts beside them.

990
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:12,120
Could Chen Mo be…

991
00:41:14,470 --> 00:41:15,310
In love?

992
00:41:32,940 --> 00:41:35,060
Fangfang! There's a box here!

993
00:41:37,500 --> 00:41:38,340
A plane?

994
00:41:39,660 --> 00:41:41,060
Why's it hidden?

995
00:41:41,820 --> 00:41:42,660
Look!

996
00:41:49,140 --> 00:41:50,460
"H-A-N,

997
00:41:50,820 --> 00:41:53,140
I promised you a special gift.

998
00:41:53,540 --> 00:41:55,580
I spent two weeks making it

999
00:41:55,580 --> 00:41:56,900
by hand.

1000
00:41:59,500 --> 00:42:00,380
How is it?

1001
00:42:00,620 --> 00:42:01,940
Isn't it special?

1002
00:42:02,060 --> 00:42:03,180
Happy birthday.

1003
00:42:04,100 --> 00:42:05,830
Now, think about how you're going to

1004
00:42:06,140 --> 00:42:07,020
repay me!

1005
00:42:11,100 --> 00:42:12,940
I didn't expect that

1006
00:42:12,940 --> 00:42:14,460
a sanctimonious

1007
00:42:14,900 --> 00:42:16,060
hypocrite like you

1008
00:42:16,340 --> 00:42:18,500
is actually not so bad."

1009
00:42:20,380 --> 00:42:21,540
A hypocrite…

1010
00:42:22,700 --> 00:42:23,620
it's probably a guy.

1011
00:42:25,700 --> 00:42:26,820
It's a plane.

1012
00:42:30,060 --> 00:42:31,700
It's also a plane.

1013
00:42:33,500 --> 00:42:34,380
Everything fits.

1014
00:42:35,940 --> 00:42:37,420
The girl in the drawing

1015
00:42:37,620 --> 00:42:38,820
is your daughter, Chen Mo,

1016
00:42:39,500 --> 00:42:41,340
and the boy next to her is that...

1017
00:42:41,340 --> 00:42:42,700
sanc... hypo...

1018
00:42:43,580 --> 00:42:45,660
Sanctimonious hypocrite.

1019
00:42:52,020 --> 00:42:55,900
(End of Episode 23)

